    Below is the description of the program:

    Power of NeuroGaming (PoNG) Center Summer Internship

    The PoNG Center is a UCSD research group that provides technology, programming, and other game-based resources to groups researching a wide variety of topics. We believe that turning data collection into a game is an effective way to engage participants and involve the community in real world solutions.

    We seek to directly engage a group of individuals who are underrepresented in the STEM workforce--individuals with developmental disorders, specifically Autism Spectrum Disorders--in a summer supported internship program. Our group and collaborators create video games for assessment and therapeutics often using technology for motion capture or other physiological data sensing
